The paper discusses the use of Fog computing for IoT in smart cities, which involves networking, distributed computing, and data analytics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the characteristics and features of Fog computing, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and open research directions, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper reviews existing research efforts, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
